This is my very first jailbreak map, so let me know how I did!

I used some elements from other maps such as the pool, and the soccer area. These are credited in the credits, along with below. I had to recreate the gameplay for them to work for the jail, and added a few elements to them to fit with the map. To play both soccer and pool just get a goal, the ball resets back to the middle of the area.

This map has several areas for people to escape, along with areas for wardens to give commands. There are many games as well. Maze, Race, Wall climb, etc. I'm not sure if wall climb has been done before, and this is my first attempt at making it popular.

To use the maze:
Have all the t's line up by the maze entrance. Go up the stairs and through the door, then click on the start button. All the t's will then run through the maze and the first person to click on the hidden red button will kill everyone in the maze. This is a good way to get the last LR, or eliminate the last 2 people down to 1.

To use the race:
Have some t's line up in front of a race entrance. Have a CT go up the stairs to the viewer box and click the start button. The doors will close when the first person gets about half way through the track. This will allow you to kill people that take to much time to start racing. Once someone reaches the end, the doors will close and kill anybody in the race arena that didn't make it!

To use the wall climb:
Have some people line up in front of a wall climb. Have a CT go up the stairs to hit the start button. The first T to the top of the wall climb will live, other contestants will die!

To use soccer and pool:
Make somewhat even teams start on each goal. When someone says, "Go", have them try to get a goal. This will take close concentration of CT's to make up rules and guidelines along with who will live etc.

To use death-pit:
Well, it's a big death hole. Use your imagination.

Just updated the map to v6.

v6 fixes up some bugs with v5.  I'm working on the next release which will focus entirely and the look and feel of the map.  This means it will come with lighting, more custom texturing, more detailing, and overall size improvements.


-----
Moderate overhaul of electric_edited_v2.  I removed/redirected the teleports that originally went to armory.  I also created a load of new secrets for CT's to help balance out that change.  One of the biggest spots is the corridor, which provides an excellent sniping point if you can figure out how to get in there.  There are actually two ways to do it.

Additional changes:
- Pool has overlook
- Replaced ugly textures with less-ugly textures
- Shower secret now accessible by just one player
- CT overlook is now glass wall instead of one-way invisible wall
- Pool is smaller
- VIP cell has hidden exit to lockers
- Soccer has two ladders to top instead of one
- Several other secrets

I apologize that I still haven't gotten to the lighting issue.  I'm working on fixing that in future releases.

Kalithan (Razor) - New map layout, FPS improvement, Thinner walls, New secrets
Monstergnom - Creator of the original ba_jail_electric maps, special thanks to him for permission to create this remake.
Toph - Soccer ball texture
Cudly - Idea for the overlook in the CT area to balance out the map between T's and CT's


I realize that this map is still fullbright, and not very detailed.  I have a friend working on the lighting right now, and I'm working on improving the details in the map.  For all of its flaws, I think this is a must for every jailbreak server.  The gameplay is extraordinary.

We are hosting this in the AHG (Afterhoursgaming.net) Jailbreak Server, and it is by far the most popular and most played map on the server! 

Again, thanks to Monstergnom for the great layout!

((ADDENDUM))
By the way, if you want the soccer ball to work properly, you'll need to have the following cvars set:

phys_pushscale 900 (Makes the ball move further when hit with a knife)
sv_turbophysics 0 (Prevents ball from passing through players)
